Interface SBaseWithDerivedUnit

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, SBase, java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    Assignment, CallableSBase, MathContainer, NamedSBaseWithDerivedUnit, Quantity, SBaseWithUnit, Variable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMathContainer, AbstractNamedSBaseWithUnit, AlgebraicRule, AssignmentRule, Compartment, Constraint, Delay, Event, EventAssignment, ExplicitRule, FunctionDefinition, InitialAssignment, KineticLaw, LocalParameter, Parameter, Priority, QuantityWithUnit, RateRule, Reaction, Rule, SBMLLevel1Rule, Species, SpeciesReference, StoichiometryMath, Symbol, Trigger

    public interface SBaseWithDerivedUnit
extends SBase
    This type represents an SBase object that is associated to a unit. This may be a directly defined unit or a unit that has to be derived by evaluating other elements within this object.
    Since:
    0.8

    • Method Detail

      • containsUndeclaredUnits

        boolean containsUndeclaredUnits()
        Returns true or false depending on whether this SBaseWithDerivedUnit refers to elements such as parameters or numbers with undeclared units. A return value of true indicates that the UnitDefinition returned by getDerivedUnitDefinition() may not accurately represent the units of the expression.
        Returns:
        true if the math expression of this SBaseWithDerivedUnit includes parameters/numbers with undeclared units, false otherwise.

      • getDerivedUnitDefinition

        UnitDefinition getDerivedUnitDefinition()
        This method derives the unit of this quantity and tries to identify an equivalent UnitDefinition within the corresponding Model. If no equivalent unit definition can be found, a new unit definition will be created that is not part of the model but represents the unit of this quantity. If it is not possible to derive a unit for this quantity, null will be returned.
        Returns:

      • getDerivedUnits

        java.lang.String getDerivedUnits()
        This method derives the unit of this quantity. If the model that contains this quantity already contains a unit that is equivalent to the derived unit, the corresponding identifier will be returned. In case that the unit cannot be derived or that no equivalent unit exists within the model, or if the model has not been defined yet, null will be returned. In case that this quantity represents a basic Unit.Kind this method will return the String representation of this Unit.Kind.
        Returns:
